  <!-- ======= 16. Design Influences ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-16">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">09</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Design Influences</h2>
      <p class="km-section-intro fade-in">Three gravitational forces shape the facility&rsquo;s visual language. Each informs a different axis: material philosophy, spatial organization, and communal energy.</p>

      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--3 stagger-children">
        <div class="km-influence km-influence--b">
          <div class="km-influence__title">LoveFrom &times; Ferrari Luce</div>
          <div class="km-influence__sub">Material restraint &middot; Typography as architecture</div>
          <p class="km-influence__text">Radical restraint over decoration. Physical controls and tactile materials over screens. No visible plastic &mdash; anodized aluminum, glass, leather, walnut. Concealed fasteners, obsessive material junctions. The simplest-looking things require the most obsessive engineering.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="km-influence km-influence--v">
          <div class="km-influence__title">Japanese Workshop</div>
          <div class="km-influence__sub">Wabi-sabi &middot; Tools as art &middot; Honest materials</div>
          <p class="km-influence__text">Nismo Omori Factory, Liberty Walk HQ, and the broader tradition where the space IS the practice. Shadow-board tool organization, shou sugi ban wood treatment, indirect lighting. The concept of &ldquo;ma&rdquo; &mdash; the beauty of negative space and the pause between actions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="km-influence km-influence--r">
          <div class="km-influence__title">F1 Pit Lane &plus; Caf&eacute; Racer</div>
          <div class="km-influence__sub">Livery logic &middot; Technical graphics &middot; Racing geometry</div>
          <p class="km-influence__text">McLaren MTC precision crossed with Rapha Clubhouse warmth. The automotive world abandoned communal spaces; cycling culture built them. Korman V2 brings the caf&eacute;-as-clubhouse model to cars &mdash; the shop as cultural meeting ground.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ======= 17. Framework ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-17">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">09</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Shot Framework</h2>
      <p class="km-section-intro fade-in">10 shot types define what the photograph IS. 7 techniques define how it&rsquo;s made. Every prompt specifies both, plus lens and base tags.</p>

      <div class="km-framework-grid stagger-children">
        <div>
          <div class="km-label">Shot Types</div>
          <div class="km-framework-item"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Wide w/ Subject for Scale</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Cover/hero shot. Establish the space, car provides human scale.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">POV</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">First-person perspective. The viewer IS the technician, the customer.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Layered Composition</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">More graphic design than photography. Color-blocking, collage thinking.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Textured Composition</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Looking down at things in detail. Ambiguates surfaces and scale.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Lifestyle Portrait</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Stage portraits. Strong direction. The subject is presented, not caught.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Environmental Portrait</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Artistic portraits in context. Expressionless, environment weight = subject weight.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Contextual Landscape</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Landscape with human element adding context to the scene.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Landscape</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Pure space, no human trace. The architecture speaks.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Natural Framing</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Architecture playing equal role. Frames within frames &mdash; doorways, glass walls.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Details</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Product, nuances. Hands, tools, the things people overlook.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="km-label">Techniques</div>
          <div class="km-framework-item"><div class="km-framework-item__title">50&amp;Stitch</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Medium format feel. Focus and depth across the entire frame.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Panorama</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Extended horizontal field. Corridors, wide workshop shots.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">D.O.F</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Shallow focus to isolate subjects. The primary detail technique.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Slow Shutter</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Motion as texture &mdash; dust motes, steam, the suggestion of movement.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">High Shutter</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Freeze motion. Exhaust gas, particles, the moment of contact.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">HDR</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">High dynamic range. Mixed light scenes, golden hour with deep shadows.</div></div>
          <div class="km-framework-item" style="margin-top:6px"><div class="km-framework-item__title">Flash</div><div class="km-framework-item__text">Museum-style single source. Clinical precision, hard shadows.</div></div>

