      </div>
      <p>Night. Through the glass garage doors &mdash; five bays dark, one bay lit. The Lachssilber M3 on the ground, hood open, sharp and still. A technician under the focused task light, movements softened to purposeful streaks by the long exposure.</p>
      <p>The car&rsquo;s paint blazes warm gold under tungsten &mdash; the salmon undertone fully alive. Widebody arches cast shadows on the polished floor, the long exposure extends the light pool into a liquid glow. Through the caf&eacute; storefront: the espresso machine&rsquo;s pilot light, the last chair pushed in. An Edward Hopper painting &mdash; isolation, focus, craft in the quiet hours.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

