  </section>

  <!-- ======= 36. Usage Notes ======= -->
  <section class="slide" id="slide-36">
    <div class="slide__inner">
      <p class="km-section-num reveal">09</p>
      <h2 class="slide__heading reveal">Usage Notes</h2>

      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--2 stagger-children">
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Hero Car Consistency</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">Every prompt references the same car &mdash; Salmon Silver / Lachssilber, widebody, #28, tri-color belt stripe, BBS mesh, Bilsteins. The Lachssilber shifts with light: cool lilac at dawn, warm gold under tungsten, full spectrum under flash, bronze under clinical dyno light. This is the point of the color choice.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Lens &amp; Technique Tags</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">Tags are per-prompt &mdash; do NOT append generic tags from earlier versions. Each prompt specifies its own lens and technique. Always append the base tags: architectural photography, editorial lighting, Fujifilm GFX 100S, photorealistic, no text overlays.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Generation Order</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">Start with: 08-A (car portrait, Flash+DOF) &rarr; 08-B (night hero, Slow Shutter) &rarr; 00-A (exterior, HDR) &rarr; 03-A (clubhouse, HDR) &rarr; 04-A (stage kits, 50&amp;Stitch) &rarr; 05-A (dyno, High Shutter) &rarr; 01-A (workshop, Panorama) &rarr; 02-C (heritage, Panorama). These establish the visual baseline.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Batch Groupings</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">Communal space prompts (03-A/B, 07-B) &mdash; generate as a set, they define cultural identity. Technical prompts (05-A/B/C) &mdash; generate together for consistent clinical tone. Atmosphere prompts (08-A/B) &mdash; pair for the dawn-to-night arc. The car appears in 21 of 25 prompts; the 4 exceptions reference it through components, swatches, or scale models.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="km-card-grid km-card-grid--2 stagger-children" style="margin-top:12px">
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Special Considerations</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">La Marzocco Linea PB + Mazzer Major is the specific espresso setup. LoveFrom influence is encoded as material philosophy, not visual style. If the model struggles with text/signage, remove text references and composite in post.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="km-rule">
          <div class="km-rule__title">Run Each Prompt Individually</div>
          <div class="km-rule__text">Don&rsquo;t combine scenes. Run individually. Always append base tags. Iterate on hero shots (08-A, 00-A, 01-A) until the facility&rsquo;s material language is established, then generate detail and atmosphere shots.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

